<subSubSection id="A22D6CA95D32954E1F039A61AA793A76" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="A8BE6AE6B122307F5B3CA3664028D15F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="029A8B4227F7B21DB9199A968FC561E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
An uncommon and local species in Greece, recorded from the floristic regions of North Central (NC) and North East (NE; 
<bibRefCitation id="AB2D98ACBADCAF24D946F330E9E5462D" author="Dimopoulos, P." journalOrPublisher="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668013" refString="Dimopoulos, P., Raus, T., Bergmeier, E., Constantinidis, T., Iatrou, G., Kokkini, S., Strid, A., D.Tzanoudakis, , 2013. Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist. Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" title="Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist" year="2013">Dimopoulos et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). This new locality on Mt. Achladovouno is probably the easternmost known so far. Other 
<taxonomicName id="85E0A8F2EF6AE1D3F0C13E6BC352D508" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Polygonatum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Polygonatum hirtum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis id="7E6043307BBE976B308CD2D2AF736028" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Polygonatum hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collections from NE include the Nomos of Chalkidiki (a.n. 1390619 LD), Serres (a.n. 10 0234511, 10 0234512 B) and Kilkis (a.n. 1324835 LD, JACQ-ID 825194, B).
</paragraph>
